“proper authority” means the person appointed by the Council for 
the  purposes  of  all  or  any  of  the  provisions  of  this  Act  where  the 
expression occurs;

(c)  if  his conduct, whether  in  connection with  his duties as a 
member of the  Council or otherwise,  has  been such as to 
bring discredit on the Council;
